{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-page-js","path":"/components/buttons/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use buttons as triggers for actions. Try to avoid the usage of buttons for navigation. The main difference between actions and navigation is that "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"actions"}]},{"type":"text","value":" are operations performed on objects, while "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"navigation"}]},{"type":"text","value":" refers to elements on the screen or view that take you to another context in the application. For navigation, consider simply using links."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pivotal UI provides four kinds of buttons: primary buttons, default buttons, danger buttons, and brand buttons. See below for examples."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"By default, each button is designed to have accessible color contrast over light backgrounds ("},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"white"}]},{"type":"text","value":" or "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"light-gray"}]},{"type":"text","value":"). To use a button over a dark background ("},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"black"}]},{"type":"text","value":" or "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"dark-gray"}]},{"type":"text","value":"), see the examples below."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"